Founding Managing Director of Democrat Newspaper and former President of the Newspaper Proprietors Association of Nigeria (NPAN), Mallam Ismaila Isa Funtua, is dead. He died of cardiac arrest Monday night. The late elder statesman was aged 76. He was life patron of Newspaper’s Proprietors Association of Nigeria (NPAN) and Chairman of Bulet International Construction Company. He will be buried according to Islamic rites Tuesday. Details later…